{"TopicId":31127,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"How do I lengthen rover bodies?","CreatedByName":"llamatoes","CreatedById":57750,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-06-03T16:09:33Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"llamatoes","CreatedById":57750,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-06-03T16:09:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI was designing a rover, and didn\u0027t have enough pace to fit everything, how do I strap two rovemates together seamlessly like in that one pre-release picture?\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222013-06-03T17:21:20Z\u0022 title=\u002206/03/2013 05:21  PM\u0022 data-short=\u002211 yr\u0022\u003EJune 3, 2013\u003C/time\u003E by llamatoes\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Poison Penguin","CreatedById":68377,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-06-03T16:15:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ETry using those struts to lengthen your craft.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"rodion_herrera","CreatedById":66284,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-06-03T16:22:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EYour friends are girders, panels, octagonal struts and nodes.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"llamatoes","CreatedById":57750,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-06-03T16:29:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI tried with cubic octagonal struts.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDidn\u0027t work.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Shrike42","CreatedById":61104,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-06-03T17:16:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EThe small i-beams can mount radially, and provide attachment points that are quite good for lengthening the wheelbase with girders.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"llamatoes","CreatedById":57750,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-06-03T17:21:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003Ethanks, its sorted now.\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}